The **print media trick** is specifically designed to load fonts asynchronously - this is a known pattern to avoid render-blocking. This technique could cause FOUT (Flash of Unstyled Text) because:
1. Page loads with no font applied (system font)
2. CSS is downloaded in background (as `media="print"` means it doesn't block rendering)
3. When CSS finishes loading, `onload` fires, removes `media="print"`, applies the font
4. Text "flashes" from system font to Google Font = FONT FLICKER/FOUT!

